      "text": "Subject may be of particular interest for energy concentration."
    },
    {
      "id": "2",
      "text": "Subject may be of particular interest for biomedical engineering concentration."
    },
    {
      "id": "3",
      "text": "Subject may be of particular interest for materials process and design concentration."
    },
    {
      "id": "4",
      "text": "Subject may be of particular interest for environmental studies concentration."
    },
    {
      "id": "5",
      "text": "In all cases, the electives must be chosen with the approval of the student’s advisor and the department. The combined list of required and elective subjects must sum to a minimum of 135 units in engineering topics (equivalent to 45 credit hours as defined by ABET).  Lists of recommended subjects for each concentration are available from the department, and additional information on current subject offerings is available in the MIT Course Catalog. Note that subjects that have been used to satisfy the foundational concepts may not also be counted toward the engineering concentration."
    },
    {
      "id": "6",
      "text": "10.490 may be repeated once for credit with permission of instructor."
    }
